</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1847 designated by Netolitzky (1943b: 61). Etymology. Unknown [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E658DA47C42719681AFCFE25ABC07A4" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="25C796A8C88E5FDC8139179EC0AB8E03" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC652765F6143D71F2EF117D137B98CE" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Northern Hemisphere, with two species in the Nearctic (
<taxonomicName id="FC20CF20074959D5D4A728C5A1630937" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planatum">
<emphasis id="2ABFA6C3232E4D0AB724BB6E42423874" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Bembidion planatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and Palaearctic (
<taxonomicName id="91124FB4EDDE80B285932DF1CC2317CF" baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1833" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altaicum">
<emphasis id="936B6B3F7644BCF9483763215F64BFDB" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Bembidion altaicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gebler in Asia) Regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B12601BA4A7762153E3AE41CE1E19B86" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="identification">
<paragraph id="54B2D3D5669DBBDCB21F32D949AA5CFC" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DDD53FC2973695D146F427C5E718B9A3" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
The North American species is treated in 
<normalizedToken id="0C91EAB16BB3272755081E208FEFD596" originalValue="Lindrothâ€™s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
(1963b: 284) monograph.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="924EEC76AC3D2DBE62D4E3B3D17AB22F" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="BC671E415C514FE58F5A46DA82D933FE" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E764663C7AEBE70BA881647EF64EF11" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
This subgenus was placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="C2E0441CC2856A13DD4FCC9736A08945" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Plataphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E161068C0D30B86902FC6DC32A37F8D9" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plataphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky by Netolitzky (1943b: 61) and Lindroth (1963b: 283) but considered a valid taxon by Toledano (2008: 12). According to Maddison (2012: 569), 
<taxonomicName id="A7DBF0D48C8A2D8DB9306FFCB657E3B7" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Melomalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EC64D6367EB3B1C388B8AED1A73194D7" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Melomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not closely related to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="F43F01AEA56CCE92A9A349B1D07D5A89" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Plataphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BC4AE8D48B3F76715BB277296498AF6" italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plataphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
